1️ Delivery Performance Insight

More than expected delivery delays were observed

A significant number of orders were delivered after the estimated delivery date

Indicates over-optimistic delivery estimates

Direct impact on customer trust and satisfaction

Business Impact:
Improving delivery estimation logic can reduce customer complaints and refunds.

2️ Estimated vs Actual Delivery Gap

Actual delivery time frequently exceeded estimated time

Large variance between promised and actual delivery days

Insight:
Logistics planning is not aligned with real operational capacity

Recommendation:
Re-calibrate ETA calculations using historical delivery data.

3️ Delay Risk Pattern

Orders with longer estimated delivery windows had higher probability of delay

Short-duration deliveries showed better accuracy

Business Meaning:
Long-distance or complex logistics routes are riskier

Action:
Flag long ETA orders as high-risk and proactively manage them.

4️ Distribution Insight

Delivery days distribution is right-skewed

Majority orders delivered within a reasonable time

Small percentage of extreme delays pull the average up

Insight:
Median delivery time is a better KPI than average

5️ Customer Experience Impact

Delayed deliveries correlate with negative customer perception

Delivery performance is a key driver of customer satisfaction

Business Insight:
Delivery speed is not just operations — it’s a customer experience metric

6️ Logistics Efficiency Insight

Estimated delivery dates are systematically optimistic

Indicates possible:

Warehouse delays

Courier inefficiencies

Underestimated last-mile delivery time

Actionable Recommendation:
Introduce buffer days for realistic delivery commitments.

7️ KPI Design Insight

Best KPIs identified:

% Delayed Deliveries

Median Delivery Days

Delivery Delay Gap (Actual − Estimated)

On-Time Delivery Rate
